For the year 62 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note27" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Cicero*.html#ref27
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">27</A>
See the
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Crassus*.html#13.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Crassus</I>, xiii.3</A>. Cicero's treatise on his <SPAN CLASS="whole">consul</SPAN>&shy;ship, there referred to, was written in Greek, and is not extant.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note28" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Cicero*.html#ref28
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">28</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Dent operam consules ne quid respublica detrimenti capiat</SPAN>
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/sall.1.html#29
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Sallust, <I>Catiline</I>, 29)</A>; <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">decrevit quondam senatus ut L. Opimius consul videret ne quid res publica detrimenti caperet</SPAN>
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/cat1.shtml#4
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Cicero, <I>in Catil.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">I</SPAN>.2.4)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note29" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Cicero*.html#ref29
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">29</A>
From Cicero's oration
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/sulla.shtml#18
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,190)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>pro Sulla</I> (6, 18)
	</A>
and
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/sall.1.html#28
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Sallust's <I>Catiline</I> (28)
	</A>
it appears that the names of these would‑be murderers were Caius Cornelius and Lucius Vargunteius.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note30" HREF="
